Minor Miracle						CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:General												PREALIGN:Deity						PRESKILL:1,Knowledge (religion)=5										PREVARGTEQ:PreStatScore_WIS,12	DESC:You can call upon your deity for a minor miracle.																																													SOURCEPAGE:p.11	BENEFIT:Choose two domains associated with your deity (if you have access to one or more domains already, the chosen domains can be the same ones you already have access to, or different ones). Once per day, by presenting a holy symbol of your deity and calling out in supplication, you can cast the 1st-level spell associated with either of the two chosen domains as a spell-like ability. You choose which domain's spell you cast at the time you use the ability. Your caster level for this effect is equal to your total Hit Dice, and the saving throw DC, if any, is Charisma-based. This spell-like ability does not not count as the ability to cast divine spells for the purposes of fulfilling prerequisites or requirements.
Reward of the Faithful					CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:General												PREALIGN:Deity						PRESKILL:1,Knowledge (religion)=1																DESC:Your intense belief in your deity allows you to benefit more from divine magic he or she provides.																																					SOURCEPAGE:p.11	BENEFIT:Whenever you are the only target of a divine spell cast by a follower of your chosen deity other than you, the spell's caster level is treated as though it were 2 higher than it actually is. Additionally, whenever you regain hit points as a result of a worshiper of your deity other than you channeling energy or casting a cure spell, you regain 1 additional hit point per die rolled for the healing gained.
Unbound Bravery						CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:General		PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Fighter ~ Bravery				PREDEITY:1,Cayden Cailean																						DESC:Your firm dedication to the principles of courage and freedom allows you to escape your bonds more easily.																														BONUS:SKILL|Escape Artist|Bravery	SOURCEPAGE:p.8	BENEFIT:You can add the bonus from bravery to Escape Artist checks and combat maneuver checks to escape a grapple. If your bonus from bravery is +2 or higher, then once per day, you can grant that bonus to an ally within 30 feet on a Will save against a fear effect, an Escape Artist check, or a combat maneuver check to escape a grapple. Granting this bonus to an ally is an immediate action and must be declared before the result of your ally's check is revealed.
Undaunted Bravery						CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:General		PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Fighter ~ Bravery				PREDEITY:1,Cayden Cailean																						DESC:It takes more than the average threat to intimidate you, and you've mastered the art of menacing your foes by implying violence through your cheerful smile.																						BONUS:SKILL|Intimidate|Bravery	SOURCEPAGE:p.8	BENEFIT:You can add your bonus from bravery to Intimidate checks and to the DC to intimidate you.

